                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 16, 1953, the Assistant Secretary of State for Public Affairs, Howland
                    Sargeant, sent a memorandum to Secretary of State-designate John Foster Dulles
                    concerning ways in which the morale and reputation of the Department of State
                    might be restored in light of Congressional attacks upon the Department’s
                    reliability. For text of this memorandum, see <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v01p1#pg_40">page 40</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
